  "description": [
    "International EDITORIAL DISCUSSION Z STATE AND LOCAL TOPICS National The Council at Work The Iran evacuation Issue is now before the Security Council the Russian delegates effort to have it deleted entirely from the agenda having been defeated by a large majority A sound principle has thus been establishedalso a valua ble precedent Yet with these sub stantial gains secure it is of less importance that consideration of Irans formal charges should begin immediately The request for a delay until April 10 made by the Russian dele gate may be reasonable For it is not impossible by any means that Mr Gromyko is not well enough prepared with documentary and other evidence also instructions from his home government to pro ceed with the case without further delay The news from Iran as well as from Moscow in the past few days indicates that the situation has been rapidly changing Stalins personal statements have been con firmed to a degree by dispatches from Iran to the effect that the Rus sian troops are moving out of the country Mr Gromykos statement that he would be unable to partici pate in any discussion of the sub stance of the Iran situation before"
